<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="744" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/147: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-18T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 18,
                                        1928—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>69. Department’s 68, December 8, 3 p.m. Department will await receipt of
                            text of French note of November 30 which it wishes to consider and
                            discuss with oil companies before sending further instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>